<section label="em-exercises">
	<title>Exercises</title>

	<aside>
		<title>Note on Variables</title>
		<p>
			In these exercises, you'll see both <m>t</m> and <m>x</m> used as the independent variable in differential equations. This is common in mathematics‚Äîthe choice of variable name doesn't change the method! Whether you see <m>y' = f(t, y)</m> or <m>y' = f(x, y)</m>, Euler's method works exactly the same way. The important thing is to consistently use the variable indicated in each problem.
		</p>
	</aside>

